b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. ChatGPT is best suited for blog posts, emails, brainstorming, general writing, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. TextCortex, meanwhile, shines for multilingual writing, content rewriting, custom AI personas, knowledge workers, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, ChatGPT describes itself as \"The most popular AI writing assistant powered by GPT-4o.\" TextCortex, established in 2021, positions itself as \"AI writing assistant with custom AI personas and knowledge bases.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **ChatGPT** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 6.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean TextCortex is a poor choice — far from it. TextCortex excels in its own right, particularly for multilingual writing and content rewriting.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value extremely versatile across writing tasks, go with ChatGPT. If custom ai personas with knowledge base uploads matters more to you, TextCortex is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
